.\" claudii manual — auto-synced to wiki via GitHub Actions
.TH CLAUDII 1 "April 1, 2026" "claudii 0.8.1" "claudii manual"
.
.SH NAME
claudii \- Fast Claude Code aliases with live model status and session insights
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B claudii
.IR command " [" args ]
.PP
When invoked with no arguments,
.B claudii
shows a contextual summary instead of the help text.
The output adapts to the current state:
an active session (cache file less than 5 minutes old) shows a compact session line
with model, context bar, cost, and rate limits;
a stale session shows the last known data;
a rate-limited state (5h usage \(>= 80%) shows a warning with the reset countdown;
and if no cache exists at all, a brief welcome message with a hint to run
.BR "claudii doctor" .
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B claudii
is a zsh plugin and CLI for Claude Code power users.
Fast aliases to launch Claude with the right model and effort,
live model health in your RPROMPT, and session insights inside Claude Code.
.
.SH INSTALL
.B Homebrew (recommended):
.PP
.RS
.nf
brew tap bmmmm/tap
brew install claudii
.fi
.RE
.PP
Add to
.IR ~/.zshrc :
.RS
.nf
source "$(brew --prefix)/opt/claudii/libexec/claudii.plugin.zsh"
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Manual:
.PP
.RS
.nf
git clone https://github.com/bmmmm/claudii ~/claudii
bash ~/claudii/install.sh
.fi
.RE
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output structured JSON instead of formatted text.
Available for:
.BR status ", " sessions ", " cost ", " trends ", " doctor ", " version .
.TP
.B \-\-tsv
Output tab-separated values (header row + data rows).
Available for:
.BR sessions ", " cost .
.PP
When stdout is not a terminal (piped or redirected) and no explicit format flag is given,
.B claudii
strips ANSI colors and prints plain text.
.B version
prints only the bare version number when piped.
.
.SH DISPLAY LAYERS
.B claudii
provides three display layers plus a session dashboard, each serving a different scope:
.TP
.B ClaudeStatus (RPROMPT)
Model health indicators rendered in the right-hand prompt of your shell.
Reads from a local cache file \(em no network calls in
.IR precmd .
The cache is refreshed automatically in the background when it exceeds
.B status.cache_ttl
seconds.
Indicators:
.B \(dg
= ok (green),
.B \(ti
= degraded (yellow),
.B \(da
= down (red),
.B ?
= API unreachable,
.B \(lB\(el\(rB
= loading (no cache),
.B \(rn
= refreshing (stale cache).
Enable with
.B claudii on
/ disable with
.BR "claudii off" .
.TP
.B Session Dashboard (above prompt)
Rendered above the prompt via the precmd hook.
Shows per-session status lines: model, context %, cost, 5h rate limit with reset countdown.
Only shown after
.B claudii
commands (not after
.B ls
or
.BR git ).
Suppressed automatically after
.BR "claudii se" / si / sessions
since those commands already display session info.
Controlled via the
.B session-dashboard.enabled
config key (values:
.BR on ", " off ;
default:
.BR off ).
.TP
.B CC-Statusline (inside Claude Code)
An info-dense metrics line rendered inside Claude Code sessions via the
.B statusLine
hook in
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Receives live JSON from Claude Code on stdin on every turn and outputs a
single formatted line.
Segments are described in detail in
.B SESSIONLINE SEGMENTS
below.
Enable with
.B claudii cc-statusline on
/ disable with
.BR "claudii cc-statusline off" .
.PP
Data flow:
.RS
.nf
Claude Code \(-> CC-Statusline (stdin JSON) \(-> cache file \(-> Session Dashboard (precmd)
                                           \(-> history.tsv (Flight Recorder)
.fi
.RE
.
.SH SESSIONLINE SEGMENTS
Each segment is separated by a dim
.B \(bv
character.
Segments are omitted when their data is absent.
.PP
Segments are also adapted to the terminal width
.RB ( $COLUMNS ):
below 60 columns only the model and context bar are shown;
60\(en80 adds cost;
80\(en100 adds rate limits;
above 100 shows everything (tokens, cache ratio, lines changed, duration).
.TP
.B Model name + effort mode
The model display name in
.B bold
(e.g.\&
.BR "claude-opus-4-5" ).
If the
.B CLAUDII_EFFORT
environment variable is set to anything other than
.BR high ,
the effort mode is appended in
.I dim
text (e.g.\&
.IR max ).
.TP
.B Context bar
A 10-character block bar showing context window usage:
.B \[u2588]
(filled) and
.B \[u2591]
(empty) characters.
Color: green < 70%, yellow 70\(en89%, red \(>= 90%.
Followed by the percentage value in dim text.
A dim
.B 1M
indicator is appended when the context window size is >= 1,000,000 tokens
(extended context mode).
.TP
.B Cost
Session cost formatted as
.B $X.XX
in cyan.
Omitted when cost is zero.
.TP
.B Tokens + cache hit ratio
Input tokens (with
.B \(ua
arrow) and output tokens (with
.B \(da
arrow) formatted with K/M suffixes (e.g.\&
.BR "15.2K\(ua 4.1K\(da" ).
When cache read tokens are present, a cache hit ratio is appended as
.B \[u26A1]XX%
(green >= 60%, yellow < 30%, dim otherwise).
.TP
.B Rate limits
5-hour and 7-day usage shown as
.B 5h:XX%
and
.B 7d:XX%
respectively.
Color: cyan < 70%, yellow 70\(en89%, red >= 90%.
Only shown when the API returns rate limit data (Pro/Max plans).
.TP
.B Lines changed
Lines added in green
.RB ( +N )
and lines removed in red
.RB ( \-N ).
Omitted when both are zero.
.TP
.B Duration
Wall-clock session duration formatted as
.BR <1m ,
.BR 5m ,
or
.B 1h 23m
(dim text).
.TP
.B Worktree / agent context
Shown in the
.B Session Dashboard
only (not in the CC-Statusline output itself).
Worktree name rendered as
.B [wt:name]
and agent context as
.B [agent:name]
in dim text.
.
.SH COMMANDS
.
.SS Aliases
Shell functions for fast Claude Code access.
Configured via
.B aliases.*
in config.
Auto-fallback to a healthy model when the configured model is down.
.
.TP
.B cl
Claude Sonnet, high effort. General-purpose default.
.TP
.B clo
Claude Opus, high effort. Complex tasks, server work.
.TP
.B clm
Claude Opus, max effort. Maximum reasoning.
.TP
.B clq
Claude Sonnet, medium effort. Search mode \(em launches in
.IR search.dir .
Equivalent to
.BR "claudii search" .
.TP
.B clh
Show the alias table and run a live model health check (current model status).
.TP
.B clorch
Example agent alias: launches Claude Opus (high effort) with the
.B orchestrate
skill as system prompt.
Configured via
.BR "claudii config set agents.clorch.*" .
See
.BR "claudii agents" .
.TP
.B cle
Example agent alias: launches Claude Sonnet (medium effort) with the
.B explorer
skill as system prompt.
Configured via
.BR "claudii config set agents.cle.*" .
See
.BR "claudii agents" .
.
.SS Display Layer Control
Global and per-layer toggles for all display components.
.
.TP
.B on
Enable all display layers at once:
ClaudeStatus RPROMPT (sets
.B statusline.enabled
to true),
Session Dashboard above prompt (sets
.B session-dashboard.enabled
to on),
and CC-Statusline inside Claude Code (writes
.B statusLine
to
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json ).
.
.TP
.B off
Disable all display layers at once.
.
.TP
.BR "claudestatus " [on|off]
Toggle only the ClaudeStatus RPROMPT.
Reads/sets
.B statusline.enabled
in config.
Without subcommand: show current state.
.
.TP
.BR "session-dashboard " [on|off]
Control the Session Dashboard (session lines above the prompt).
Without subcommand: show current state.
.RS
.TP
.B on
Enable the session dashboard.
.TP
.B off
Disable the session dashboard.
.RE
.IP
.BR "dashboard " [on|off]
Deprecated alias for
.BR "session-dashboard" .
Still works for backwards compatibility.
.
.TP
.BR "cc-statusline " [on|off]
Toggle only the CC-Statusline inside Claude Code.
Modifies
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Without subcommand: show current state.
.
.TP
.B layers
Show component overview: ClaudeStatus (RPROMPT), Session Dashboard (above prompt),
CC-Statusline (inside Claude Code). Includes current status, config, data flow,
and a reference legend for all symbols and fields used in the output.
.PP
.B Session Dashboard symbols:
.PP
.RS
.nf
\[u25CF]    active           session or service is active
\[u25CB]    inactive         session ended or service is off
\[u2588]\[u2591]  context bar      context window fill (8 blocks = 100%)
\[u26A1]    cache ratio      % of input served from prompt cache
|    separator        field separator (dim)
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B CC-Statusline fields:
.PP
.RS
.nf
\[u2588]\[u2591]  context bar      context window fill (10 blocks = 100%)
$    cost             session cost USD
5h:  5h rate limit    token budget used %
7d:  7d rate limit    token budget used %
\[u21BA]    reset            minutes until rate limit refreshes
\[u2191]    input tokens     tokens sent to model this session
\[u2193]    output tokens    tokens received from model
\[u26A1]    cache ratio      % of input served from prompt cache
+/-  lines changed    code added / removed
     duration         total session time
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ClaudeStatus (RPROMPT) indicators:
.PP
.RS
.nf
\[u2713]    ok               model operational
\[u26A0]    degraded         partial outage
\[u2717]    down             major outage
\[u27F3]    refreshing       background check running
?    unreachable      status.claude.com not reachable
.fi
.RE
.
.SS ClaudeStatus
Live model health monitoring in your shell RPROMPT.
Uses the Statuspage components API; falls back to the RSS feed for per-model incident details.
.
.TP
.B status
Live model health check (always bypasses the cache).
Displays a per-model status table with icons and labels for each configured model
(ok \(en green, degraded \(en yellow, down \(en red, unknown \(en dim).
Shows the time since the last check and the configured refresh interval.
Supports
.B \-\-json
(array of model/status objects).
.
.TP
.BR status " 5m|15m|30m|60m"
Set the background cache refresh interval (default: 15m).
Values below 30s are rejected.
.
.PP
RPROMPT indicators:
.B \(dg
= ok (green),
.B \(ti
= degraded (yellow),
.B \(da
= down (red),
.B ?
= API unreachable.
.B \(lB\(el\(rB
= loading (no cache),
.B \(rn
= refreshing (stale cache).
.
.SS Session Dashboard
Rendered in the shell above the prompt line via
.IR precmd .
Reads per-session cache files written by the CC-Statusline handler.
Shows per-session lines: model name, context %, cost, 5h rate limit with reset countdown.
Only shown after
.B claudii
commands; suppressed after
.BR "se" / si / sessions
since those already display session info.
.PP
Data flow:
.RS
Claude Code \(-> CC-Statusline (stdin JSON) \(-> cache file \(-> Session Dashboard (precmd)
.RE
.
.SS CC-Statusline
Rendered inside Claude Code sessions via
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Shows model name, context usage bar, cost, token counts, rate limits,
lines changed, session duration, worktree name, and agent context in a single info-dense line.
.
.TP
.B cc-statusline
Show whether the CC-Statusline is active.
.
.TP
.B "cc-statusline on"
Add the CC-Statusline to
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Restart Claude Code to activate.
.
.TP
.B "cc-statusline off"
Remove the CC-Statusline from
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
.
.SS Sessions and Cost
.
.TP
.B sessions
List active and recent Claude Code sessions with model, context usage,
cost, rate limits, worktree name, and agent context.
Shows per-session details and an aggregate summary.
A third line per session shows the fingerprint: top-5 files accessed via tool calls,
formatted as
.BR "name(N) name(N) ..."
(omitted when no JSONL transcript is available).
Sessions are detected from cache files written by the CC-Statusline handler.
Supports
.B \-\-json
(array of session objects with
.BR fingerprint " and " last_user_message
fields) and
.B \-\-tsv
(tab-separated rows).
.
.TP
.BI "sessions \-\-resume " id
Resume a Claude Code session by ID.
Equivalent to
.BR "claude --resume " id .
The session ID can be obtained from
.B claudii se
(shown as the first 8 characters of the session ID in the detail line).
Alias:
.BR "se --resume " id .
.
.TP
.B sessions-inactive
Show inactive (ended or stale) Claude Code sessions.
Lists sessions that are no longer active, with age, context usage, and rate-limit data.
Alias:
.BR si .
.
.TP
.B cost
Aggregate session costs from the session cache.
Shows a per-model breakdown and total for today (sessions written in the last 24 hours)
and all time.
Session cache files are read from
.IR "${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii/session-*"
(overrideable via
.BR CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR ).
Supports
.B \-\-json
(object with today/alltime breakdown) and
.B \-\-tsv
(period/model/cost/sessions rows).
.
.TP
.B trends
Weekly and daily cost trends from persistent history (Flight Recorder).
The CC-Statusline handler appends a line to
.I ~/.cache/claudii/history.tsv
on every update.
.B trends
reads this file, deduplicates by session (takes the max cost per session_id),
and shows a per-day breakdown for the current week, a total for last week,
a 30-day model distribution split, and the costliest day.
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
.
.SS Config
.
.TP
.B config
Show all config values.
.
.TP
.BI "config get " key
Read a config value using dot-notation.
Example:
.BR "claudii config get aliases.cl.model" .
.
.TP
.BI "config set " "key value"
Set a config value.
Example:
.BR "claudii config set statusline.models opus,sonnet" .
.
.TP
.B "config reset"
Reset all config to defaults.
.
.TP
.BI "config export " "[file]"
Print config as JSON, or write to
.I file
if specified.
.
.TP
.BI "config import " file
Replace current config with a JSON file (backs up the existing config first).
.
.TP
.B "config theme"
List available color themes.
The active theme is marked with an asterisk.
.
.TP
.BI "config theme " name
Set the active theme by name.
Available themes:
.B default
(magenta accent, standard ANSI colors) and
.B pastel
(softer 256-color palette).
The theme name is stored as
.B theme.name
in
.IR config.json .
Unknown theme names print an error and exit non-zero.
.
.SS Watch
Background watcher that monitors session cache files and sends a macOS notification
when a 5-hour rate limit resets.
Uses
.B terminal-notifier
if installed, otherwise falls back to
.BR osascript .
The watcher polls every 60 seconds and only notifies once per reset timestamp.
The process ID is stored in
.IR "${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii/watch.pid" .
.
.TP
.B watch
Start the background watcher (same as
.BR "watch start" ).
.
.TP
.B "watch start"
Start the background watcher.
Prints the PID and exits immediately.
Does nothing if a watcher is already running.
.
.TP
.B "watch stop"
Stop the background watcher and remove the PID file.
.
.TP
.B "watch status"
Show whether the watcher is running and its PID.
.
.TP
.B "watch test"
Send a test notification immediately to verify that notifications work.
Useful for checking
.B watch.sound
configuration.
.
.TP
.B "watch volume"
Show the current notification volume (0\(en100).
.
.TP
.BI "watch volume " N
Set the notification volume to
.I N
(0\(en100).
Example:
.BR "claudii watch volume 75" .
.
.TP
.B "watch sound"
Show the current notification sound file path, or
.B (default)
if none is set.
.
.TP
.BI "watch sound " file
Set a custom sound file to play on notification.
The file must exist.
Example:
.BR "claudii watch sound /System/Library/Sounds/Glass.aiff" .
.
.TP
.B "watch sound default"
Reset the notification sound to the system default (no custom sound file).
.
.SS Agents
.
.TP
.B agents
List configured agents (alias \(-> skill mapping) or show onboarding instructions.
Agents let you launch Claude with a specific skill as the system prompt using a short
alias instead of a long
.B \-\-append\-system\-prompt
flag.
.PP
When agents are configured in
.I config.json
under the
.B agents
key, a left-aligned table is shown:
.RS
.nf
ALIAS     SKILL         MODEL   EFFORT
clorch    orchestrate   opus    high
cle       explorer      sonnet  medium
.fi
.RE
.PP
Followed by the hint: \(dqType the alias to launch.\(dq
.PP
When no agents are configured, an onboarding message is shown with the equivalent
manual command, setup instructions, and a list of skills found in
.I .claude/skills/*/SKILL.md
in the current directory.
.PP
Supports
.B \-\-json
(array of objects with
.BR alias ", " skill ", " model ", " effort
fields).
.PP
Configure agents via:
.RS
.nf
claudii config set agents.clorch.skill orchestrate
claudii config set agents.clorch.model opus
claudii config set agents.clorch.effort high
.fi
.RE
.
.SS System
.
.TP
.BI "search " "['query']"
Launch Claude Code in the configured search directory
.RI ( search.dir " in config, default:" " ~/claude-search" ).
Uses the
.B clq
alias settings.
If
.I query
is provided, it is passed as the initial prompt.
.
.TP
.B restart
Reload the plugin by sourcing
.IR ~/.zshrc .
Stays in the current directory.
.
.TP
.B update
Update claudii to the latest version.
Auto-detects the install method:
if
.B CLAUDII_HOME
is under the Homebrew prefix, runs
.BR "brew upgrade claudii" ;
if it is a git repository, runs
.BR "git pull --ff-only" ;
otherwise prints instructions for both methods and exits with an error.
After updating, run
.B claudii restart
to reload the plugin.
.
.TP
.B version
Print the version string and about info when running interactively.
When piped (stdout is not a terminal), prints the bare version number without the
.B "claudii v"
prefix.
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
.
.TP
.B changelog
Shows release notes for the current version from CHANGELOG.md.
Alias:
.BR about .
.
.TP
.B doctor
Run an installation health check.
Verifies that Claude Code and jq are installed,
that the CC-Statusline is configured in
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json ,
that the cache directory exists,
that completions are present,
and that the plugin is loaded.
Also reports the installed version.
Supports
.B \-\-json
(array of check result objects with
.BR check ", " status ", " detail
fields).
.
.SH SHORTCUTS
Shorthands expand to their full command before processing.
.PP
.TS
l l.
s	status
se	sessions
ss	sessions
si	sessions-inactive
c	cost
t	trends
d	doctor
about	changelog
.TE
.PP
Example:
.B claudii s
is identical to
.BR "claudii status" .
.
.SH CONFIG FILE
User config:
.I ~/.config/claudii/config.json
(or
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/claudii/config.json
if set).
Created automatically from defaults on first run.
.PP
Key paths (dot-notation):
.PP
.RS
.nf
aliases.cl.model        model for \fBcl\fR (default: sonnet)
aliases.cl.effort       effort for \fBcl\fR (default: high)
aliases.clo.model       model for \fBclo\fR (default: opus)
aliases.clm.effort      effort for \fBclm\fR (default: max)
aliases.clq.model       model for \fBclq\fR / search (default: sonnet)
fallback.enabled        auto-fallback on outage (default: true)
fallback.opus.model     fallback model when opus is down
status.cache_ttl        cache TTL in seconds (default: 900)
statusline.enabled      ClaudeStatus in RPROMPT (default: true)
statusline.models       models to monitor (default: opus,sonnet,haiku)
session-dashboard.enabled  session dashboard mode (default: off; values: on/off)
debug.level             log level (default: off)
search.dir              search directory (default: ~/claude-search)
watch.sound             path to a sound file played on notification (default: empty = no sound)
watch.volume            notification sound volume, 0\(en100 (default: 50)
.fi
.RE
.
.SH STATUS CACHE
The model status cache is stored at
.IR "${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii/status-models"
(overrideable via
.BR CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR ).
It persists across terminal sessions and reboots.
It contains one line per model:
.PP
.RS
.nf
opus=ok
sonnet=down
haiku=ok
.fi
.RE
.PP
The cache is refreshed automatically in the background when it exceeds
.B status.cache_ttl
seconds.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDII_HOME
Path to the plugin directory. Set automatically.
.TP
.B CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR
Override the cache directory (default:
.IR ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii ).
.TP
.B CLAUDII_LOG_LEVEL
Override the debug log level (off, error, warn, info, debug).
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Overrides the config directory (default:
.IR ~/.config ).
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
Overrides the base cache directory (default:
.IR ~/.cache ).
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/claudii/config.json
User configuration.
.TP
.I $CLAUDII_HOME/config/defaults.json
Shipped defaults (read-only reference).
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/status-models
Per-model status cache.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/session-*
Per-session cache files written by the CC-Statusline handler.
Contains model, context percentage, cost, and rate limit data.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/history.tsv
Persistent session history (Flight Recorder).
TSV file with one line per CC-Statusline update:
timestamp, model, cost, context percentage, 5-hour rate, session_id.
Read by
.BR "claudii trends" .
.TP
.I ~/.claude/settings.json
Claude Code settings, modified by
.BR "claudii cc-statusline" .
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Enable all display layers:
.B claudii on
.TP
Live health check:
.B claudii status
.TP
Toggle only ClaudeStatus:
.B claudii claudestatus off
.TP
Toggle only Session Dashboard:
.B claudii session-dashboard on
.TP
Toggle only CC-Statusline:
.B claudii cc-statusline on
.TP
Check every 5 minutes:
.B claudii status 5m
.TP
Component overview:
.B claudii layers
.TP
Publish a release:
.B bash scripts/release.sh 0.7.0
.TP
Dry-run to verify pre-flight checks:
.B bash scripts/release.sh 0.7.0 \-\-dry-run
.TP
Read a config value:
.B claudii config get aliases.cl.model
.
.SH VISUAL LANGUAGE
claudii uses a consistent set of symbols across all output:
.PP
.TS
l l l.
Symbol	Meaning	Color
_
\(bu	active session	green
\(ci	ended / inactive	dim
\(tf	warning (rate limit, stale cache)	yellow
\(mu	error / failure	red
\(OK	ok / success	green
\(da	down (model unavailable)	red
~	degraded (partial outage)	yellow
|	separator	\(em
\[u2588]	progress bar \(em filled block	context-sensitive
\[u2591]	progress bar \(em empty block	dim
.TE
.PP
The helper function
.B _claudii_sym
.RI ( lib/visual.sh )
accepts a name
.RB ( active ", " inactive ", " warn ", " error ", " ok ", " down ", " degraded ", " sep )
and prints the corresponding colored symbol.
Constants are prefixed
.B CLAUDII_SYM_
(symbols) and
.B CLAUDII_CLR_
(ANSI colors).
.
